        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Mr Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philada</placeName>!</p>
            <p>Rev. Sir! Our heartfelt thank to you for your kindly<lb/> regard of our'n<add>?</add>
                by sending the Occident to us.<lb/> Please accept my name as a subscriber to
                your<lb/> far spread Paper. In about two weeks I shall call<lb/> at your office for
                to pay the same.</p>
            <p>Our new Synagogue was duly consecrated, the notices about<lb/> the same, which are
                given in by following Paper you<lb/> will please and copy in the Occident, with the
                especially<lb/> remark, that in the <sic>evining</sic> after the Consecration
                the<lb/> members of the Congregation <sic>maid</sic> in a body a visit to me<lb/>
                where <persName>Mr Burnstein</persName>, a well educated young man <del>maid</del>
                delivered<lb/> an eloquent Address and representing to me one Dozen<lb/> of fine
                silver table spoons, engraved in a <sic>verry</sic> remark<lb/> able manner. Our
                congregation is in a prosperous condition<lb/> and by coming of <persName>Mr
                    Lissner</persName> of <placeName><sic>Sax Meiningen</sic></placeName>, for
                who<lb/> we wrote to take charge of the Ministership we shall<lb/> surely get a fine
                    <add>קהל</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Yours Sir most obedient</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Michael Putzel</persName>.</p>
            <p><placeName>Easton</placeName>, <date>April 25. 1851</date>.</p>
            <p>P.S. The Officers elect by the last</p>
            <p>G. M. are:</p>
            <list type="simple">
                <head/>
                <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>M. Putzel</persName> Pres.</item>
                <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>Israel Ullman</persName> Treasurer</item>
                <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>Liebman Traugott</persName> Secy.</item>
                <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>Moses Cohn</persName> &amp; <persName>Henry
                        Ballinger</persName> Trustees.</item>
            </list>
            <p>and then 6 Deputies, which officers have to lead the transactions of
                <add>קהל</add>.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Editor of the Occident</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>118 South Fourth Street</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Philada.</placeName>
            </p>
